From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Subject: [PATCH] nfc: hci: shdlc: gate the frame hexdumps behind dynamic-debug

SHDLC_DUMP_SKB() dumped every SHDLC I-frame (tx) and every incoming frame (rx)
with print_hex_dump(KERN_DEBUG, ...). print_hex_dump() ALWAYS writes to the
kernel ring buffer regardless of the console loglevel, so on steelhead — where a
userspace daemon polls the pn544 continuously for NFC tap-to-send — the boot log
and journal fill with hundreds of "shdlc: 00000000: .." lines every boot.

Switch to print_hex_dump_debug(), which is a no-op unless CONFIG_DYNAMIC_DEBUG
(or per-file DEBUG) is enabled — neither is on this image — so the frame dumps
vanish from the ring buffer/journal while staying one dynamic-debug toggle away
when actually debugging SHDLC. The paired pr_debug("%s:\n") is already gated the
same way.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
 net/nfc/hci/llc_shdlc.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/net/nfc/hci/llc_shdlc.c
+++ b/net/nfc/hci/llc_shdlc.c
@@ -101,7 +101,7 @@
 #define SHDLC_DUMP_SKB(info, skb)				  \
 do {								  \
 	pr_debug("%s:\n", info);				  \
-	print_hex_dump(KERN_DEBUG, "shdlc: ", DUMP_PREFIX_OFFSET, \
+	print_hex_dump_debug("shdlc: ", DUMP_PREFIX_OFFSET, \
 		       16, 1, skb->data, skb->len, 0);		  \
 } while (0)
